HEADWORD: Unshell
<hw>Un*shell"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>shell</ets>.]</ety> <def>To strip the shell from;
to take out of the shell; to hatch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

